The Echo Pop in Midnight Teal is a remarkable compact smart speaker that seamlessly blends style and functionality. Designed to fit effortlessly into any space, this speaker boasts a full sound experience that is bound to captivate your senses. With built-in Alexa integration, it offers a world of convenience and entertainment at your fingertips.The first thing that catches your eye is its stunning Midnight Teal color, adding a touch of elegance to any room. The compact design doesn't compromise on sound quality, delivering rich and clear audio that belies its size.Equipped with Alexa, Amazon's virtual assistant, the Echo Pop becomes your personal concierge. Whether you want to play your favorite tunes, set reminders, check the weather, or control smart home devices, Alexa is ready to assist. The hands-free voice control offers a seamless experience, making your daily tasks effortless and enjoyable.Despite its compact form, the Echo Pop's sound performance is impressive. It fills the room with a vibrant sound that enhances your music, podcasts, or even conference calls. The versatile speaker is equally at home delivering energetic beats or mellow melodies, ensuring you enjoy your audio content to the fullest.Setting up the Echo Pop is a breeze, and its compatibility with various streaming services ensures you can enjoy your preferred content without limitations. The sleek touch controls on the top of the speaker add a modern touch, allowing you to adjust volume, skip tracks, or mute the microphone with a simple tap.The Echo Pop's connectivity options are comprehensive, with Bluetooth and Wi-Fi enabling effortless pairing with your devices. The speaker can also be part of a multi-room audio setup, creating an immersive experience throughout your home.In conclusion, the Echo Pop in Midnight Teal is a masterful blend of design and functionality. Its compact size, full sound capabilities, Alexa integration, and versatile connectivity options make it a standout smart speaker. Whether you're a music enthusiast, a smart home aficionado, or simply looking to elevate your audio experience, the Echo Pop is a compelling choice that combines aesthetics and technology flawlessly.

For the size, the sound is really good. This is my first use of a this kind of gadget so I haven't really explore all functionalities. I think I am still getting use with Alexa speaking every time there's an activity. ^_^

It seems to work very well. I have bought some Moross smart plugs to go with it to control a number of different devices and they were all easy to set up. The Echo Pop communicates well with them, even in other rooms. Very happy with it.

Easy to setup and responds much better than my old Google Home device. Only wish more names were allowed than the 5 it comes with. Having a British male as a voice is great, we order a butler around rather than a female!

I got an echo pop to test out as they were only 20 bucks. It's a great product. You can control all smart devices and use apps like Spotify from it. You can even set alarms, reminders and it notifies you of your notifications and makes calls etc if you upload your contacts. Fantastic product.

I like it. It’s a cute little speaker. I’ve popped it on my bedside so I can control my Philips Hue lights easily and play rain sounds etc for sleep, alarms and notification’s.As expected, It is not super powerful but it has a nice crisp sound and decent volume.Connected fine, painless setup.Picks up and understands my voice well.You can easily turn off the listening part of the device if you need privacy.

The echo pop just replaced my google mini. I purchased the Echo pop with a low expectation of its sound quality and expected it to sound very thin like the google mini. However I was surprised by the decent bass this tiny speaker is capable of pumping out! You can use the equilizer in the settings to add more bass if you wish. Yes the speaker is very directional, but like in my case, it's ideal for an office table. Alexa as always is very responsive and the light bar is attractive. I wish there was a setting to keep the status light on like a night light, hopefully they will add a feature like that in the future. Overall really happy with my purchase!
Have so enjoyed having this in our home, Our first experience of Alexa and our grandkids love it too.
Love my new Echo Dot. Thank you Amazon.
I love my echo pop. I used it for music, audible stories, setting alarms. Checking weather etc.

My AJAX ECO Multi-purpose Antibacterial Wipes (110 wipes) arrived on time and are in good condition. Thanks to Amazon (Au) for speedily dispatching my order and Amazon Logistics for their fast doorstep delivery.I purchased this pack of AJAX SINGLE wipes in a "you beat" Amazon Deal. Usually, I shop for the least expensive alternative as they are a relatively homogeneous product: they contain similar quantities of the active antibacterial ingredient. I purchased this pack in June 21 and the expiry date is in October 22.AJAX ECO wipes are significant different in that the base cloth material is manufactured from environmentally sustainable bamboo. Most other brands of antibacterial wipes use a synthetic material with potential pollution issues. AJAX wipes will compost down and add to soil fertility.AJAX wipes come in sealed plastic packs with a flip top dispenser. The seal underlying the flip top dispenser helps to keep the wipes fresh by retaining the enclosed disinfectant liquid. Before use, peel the seal away,  don't discard but reseal after each use to help maintain freshness. Also, remember to keep the dispenser top closed to further help retain freshness, when not in use. I find that frequent brief multiple daily turning (dispenser closed) of the pack assists in keeping the wipes evenly moist, particularly when numerous wipes still remain.Every AJAX ECO antibacterial wipe is for SINGLE USE ONLY and are definitely NOT FLUSHABLE (eg via the toilet). Each wipe has the approx dimensions 22.5cm × 17cm. I find that each wipe has sufficient moisture to clean and treat a dry sealed area (counter top) of approx 1.5 square metres. However, the wipes contain insufficient moisture to dissolved or loosen dried accumulated food deposits. Also, the wipes don't remove most stains (eg cordial or tea). The integrity of the cloth is maintained throughout use. There are no apparent residues or lint on surfaces after use.I use these wipes daily to clean and disinfect counter tops (kitchen and bathroom) and water taps, door handles, remote controls and mobile phones. I, also, use them for small clean-ups in the bathroom (toilet pan , cistern, seat and floor), wiping out home bins and lined cupboards.AJAX ECO wipes effectively clean and bacterially disinfect surfaces. The wipes are, also, very convenient for quick clean-ups.
i love these wipes and i’ve been getting them for ages on subscription but omg! my recent renewal cost more than double my last one!!

i love how these are biodegradable and they work perfect but they are pretty dry and they don't really go THAT far wet, but if you spray extra disinfectant you can make it last longer and super convenient to just toss out all the dust or when dealing with really mucky surfaces. The plastic packaging around the book was ripped a bit and as a result of that, the corner that the plastic was ripped in was a bit folded. Although it’s not a big issue, the book should still come in great condition since it’s new. I don’t mind it that much but some people might.

Though well-written, this book seems to be more of a rather premature autobiography of a 20-something year old wealthy white male.Granted, he has overcome some first-world adversity, but I found the underlying message to be repetitive and better suited to teenagers or young adults who lack drive and direction.The underlying message, over and over (and over) is to persist with positive behaviours and they will eventually become a habit.It is well-studied that if you repeat an action 27 days in a row, it becomes a habit. That is the general crux of this book and I thought this was something most people already knew.It also appeared to me that the author has lived quite a privileged life and doesn't seem to yet understand what lifelong adversity is via lower to middle-class cards most of us are dealt in life, so if you are 30+ and have suffered many setbacks in life because you didn't win the 'family lottery', you will likely find this book mildly irritating.I personally found this book useless as I do not lack drive or ambition at all and unfortunately can't relate to a wealthy high-school jock who hurt himself playing a notoriously dangerous sport.I'll probably keep it for when my son starts reading novels.

These are invaluable as tracking devices but if you want to use these as an anti theft tracker removing the speaker is essential but easily do-able. Problem with these devices is they can’t be shared so the family pet for example, can only be tracked by one apple account.  Family sharing I thought would have been invaluable

They look great, and work well - as long as you have people with apple products passing by. I had a car parked in a car park and it did not know as for hrs no one passed close enough with an apple product to uplink the info. But all in all they are great ! especially for luggage. or tracking things in crowded places.

The tags are good. Apple has one of the largest network helping to trace the items. I have attached one to my Son's school bag. I do get updates about his location but its not a continuous location tracker and may be unsuitable for tracking lost kids or pets (this is mainly due to anti stalking features). Also, it depends upon apple devices being present in the area to detect the tag. If you lose something where there is no phone coverage / apple devices, this will be of no use. The tag is not very thin (around 3 coins thick) so not suitable for placing it in men's wallet unless the wallet has a suitable cavity to accommodate it. Please consider this before buying if that's your intent. Second, there are a lot of cheap silicone keyrings available to attach these to keys and other items, however these are not reliable at all and the tag can fall out easily. You need to spend at least 20$ per tag to attach it reliably to your items. Depending upon the value, I still think this is reasonable for items such as keys and laptop backpacks, however I wish apple made the tags with a hole at least so that  it could be attached directly if needed instead of buying third party accessories. I have deducted one star for this reason.
